result.name: Chin Chin Thai Cuisine

reviews.text:
Environment & Atmosphere - The location is near the residence and commercial building so in the peak hours during the weekday. The arrangement of the restaurant is they only allow you have one hour to finish your meal. You have to expect there will be very noisy inside but the lighting there still make you feel relax. So far I can say there’s no surprise for me. 

Food - Taste and the way they cook is traditional Thai dishes. Food arrive very fast, maybe there’s the reason that it’s peak hour and they have to serve food so that they can get an another round table for the next customer.

Menu - Weekday lunch hour only offer lunch set menu, you can’t order anything that’s extra or outside the lunch set menu.

Price - a set is around HKD70-90. Include a drink so the price is kind of reasonable.
Very poor service, waiter came 6x to change the order. We also had to eat curry directly from bowl and got no drinks. Food quality was average.
Unbelievably slow and poor service. I waited my Pad Thai for 35 mins and it arrived with completely cold prawns on it. This is totally unacceptable. Not to mention the below-average quality food.
Nice place, good food. Terrible service - they mixed up our order.

Food is good and delicious but u need to book in advance as seating is limited if u don’t want to seat near the kitchen 

I like the coconut rice as a this is fried rice with seafood on top 

The garlic bread is perfect matched with curry and highly recommend to eat together

result.name: Chin Chin Thai Cuisine

reviews.text: 食物不錯，但份量少。我們於7時45分落單，要一份四人套餐，約25分後才獲通知没有我們想吃的魚和鷄，结果要取消套餐，重新落單，又再多等20分才開始上食物。另外，不要期待有什麼服務，我們要求侍應調較冷氣，她竟然話不懂，叫我們自己找部長，我們找部長，又要再三催促，才獲處理要求，令人氣結。
地點方便，環境舒服，食品很有水準。羊架、豬頸肉烤得很好。原個椰青焗飯，清甜好味。烤薄牛肉沙律也不錯。船麵也出色。青檸梳打水就太甜了。香茅奶茶ok幾新奇。
禮貌差！服務差！食品與圖片相差太大！牛柳粒炒飯的牛柳少！價格不便宜，又偷工減料！千萬不要來

The arrangement of the restaurant is they only allow you have one hour to finish your meal. You have to expect there will be very noisy inside but the lighting there still make you feel relax. So far I can say there’s no surprise for me. 

Food - Taste and the way they cook is traditional Thai dishes. Food arrive very fast, maybe there’s the reason that it’s peak hour and they have to serve food so that they can get an another round table for the next customer.

Menu - Weekday lunch hour only offer lunch set menu, you can’t order anything that’s extra or outside the lunch set menu.

Price - a set is around HKD70-90. Include a drink so the price is kind of reasonable.
食物一般，招呼不合格，剛吃完餐就來小動作暗示顧客结賬。
